This is a Typescript project is named redis-mcp. It is a CLI tool starts nodejs server compatable with the Model Context Protocol (MCP) and provides access to a Redis database.

See @https://modelcontextprotocol.io/introduction and https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/concepts/tools for an introduction to Model Context Protocol (MCP).

Clients like Claude Desktop and Cline connect to this MCP server using configuration like:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "redis": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["<location of the script>/redis_server.js"],
      "disabled": false
    }
  }
}